cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with the recognition of visibility graphs of polygons, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves complexity theory and the study of complete problems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of real polynomials and quantifier-free formulas also indicates a possible connection to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
